CHANDLER, Ariz. (AP) _ Microchip Technology Inc. (MCHP) on Monday reported fiscal fourth-quarter profit of $437.9 million.On a per-share basis, the Chandler, Arizona-based company said it had profit of 77 cents. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs and stock option expense, were $1.35 per share.The results exceeded Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of 11 analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $1.25 per share.The chipmaker posted revenue of $1.84 billion in the period, also surpassing Street forecasts. Nine analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $1.82 billion.For the year, the company reported profit of $1.29 billion, or $2.27 per share. Revenue was reported as $6.82 billion.For the current quarter ending in July, Microchip Tech expects its per-share earnings to range from $1.32 to $1.36. Analysts surveyed by Zacks had forecast adjusted earnings per share of $1.28.ADVERTISEMENTThe company said it expects revenue in the range of $1.92 billion to $1.99 billion for the fiscal first quarter. Analysts surveyed by Zacks had expected revenue of $1.85 billion._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on MCHP at https://www.zacks.com/ap/MCHP